      "content": "## Job Posting + Matching Flow (Feb 10, 2026 — COMPLETE)\n**Recruiter-side**:\n- **Kanban pipeline board**: 7 canonical stages, bulk actions (archive/advance/reject), filter/sort\n- **Skills analysis**: AI breakdown of required vs matched candidate skills per application\n- **Activity feed**: Job creation, application state changes, bulk actions logged\n\n**Candidate-side**:\n- **\"Recommended for You\"**: Algorithm matches candidate skills against open job requirements\n- **Match %**: Skill-based scoring + missing skills highlighted on job cards\n- **Pipeline stages**: Aligned across all jobs; standardized state transitions\n\n**Backend**:\n- **7-stage pipeline**: Applied, Screening, Phone Screen, Technical, Offer, Accepted, Rejected (canonical)\n- **Skills matching**: Compares `candidate_skills` against JD-parsed requirements; calculates matching/missing/extra\n- **Validation**: Pipeline stage names enforced; application state transitions validated\n- **Activity wiring**: All state changes (job create, application moved, bulk actions) logged to `activity_log`",
      "relevance": "95%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 3,
      "layer_name": "Cross-Company Patterns",
      "header": "CI/CD & GitHub Integration",
      "content": "### CI/CD & GitHub Integration\n- **CI workflow in PostgreSQL 15 + full test suite**: GitHub Actions CI validates Express + PostgreSQL apps; includes startup validation, RLS policy regression, smoke tests, unit tests, integration tests; fast fail on any test failure; prevents broken code merging to main\n- **Branch protection requires passing CI**: Set branch protection rule on main requiring passing workflow status checks before PR merge allowed; blocks broken code from landing; works after CI workflow pushed to GitHub\n- **GitHub token workflow scope requirement**: GitHub PAT must include `workflow` scope to push files to `.github/workflows/` directory; repos with strict token permissions may block workflow file pushes; platform limitations can prevent CI setup despite code being ready; documented workaround: owner can manually push via git CLI with full-scope token\n- **CI workflow deployment readiness**: When workflow is committed locally but push blocked by token limitations, document status in `CI-SETUP-STATUS.md` including commit hash, workflow file location, and exact error; notify owner of two paths forward (platform fix or manual push); task remains complete if work is done and blocker is external\n- **GitHub API access limitations**: Automation cannot directly enable branch protection or create PRs via GitHub API; requires manual GitHub UI steps or PAT with full API scope; feature requests for direct platform API access documented and tracked\n- **RLS enforcement in CI via dedicated role**: Create non-BYPASSRLS role (`planxpress_rls_test`) with minimal table permissions (SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE); run RLS regression tests against this role to verify policies block unauthorized access; prevents false-greens from admin-level testing; idempotent role creation script (`scripts/ci/create-rls-test-role.js`) runs after migrations in CI pipeline\n- **RLS test enforcement mode**: RLS regression test script accepts `DATABASE_URL_RLS_TEST` env var pointing to dedicated non-BYPASSRLS connection; when set, tests run with strict enforcement; exits with error if BYPASSRLS detected without enforcement connection (fail-closed behavior); prevents fallback to admin role if enforcement connection misconfigured\n- **RLS test skip hardening**: RLS regression tests fail hard if any tables are skipped (no partial validation allowed); skipped tables masked RLS policy gaps historically; exit code 1 on any skip ensures CI catches coverage gaps; enhanced logging indicates which tables require policy review\n- **RLS multi-tenant test harness**: GUC variable `app.tenant_id` set via parameterized `set_config('app.tenant_id', $1, true)` at transaction-start establishes tenant context; third parameter `true` makes setting transaction-local (like SET LOCAL); RLS policies query `current_setting('app.tenant_id')` to enforce row visibility; allows CI to test isolation between tenant A/B in same test suite without connection pooling; fixture setup uses privileged connection to insert parent records (e.g., forecast_runs) before child records (e.g., staffing_plans with required NOT NULL FKs); avoids unique constraint conflicts by generating unique IDs per test iteration\n- **Postgres 15 parameter safety**: String interpolation in raw SQL (e.g., `SET LOCAL app.tenant_id = '${value}'`) fails in PostgreSQL 15; use parameterized `set_config()` function with placeholders instead; `set_config('app.tenant_id', $1, true)` is safe across all Postgres versions and maintains prepared statement semantics",
      "relevance": "45%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 3,
      "layer_name": "Cross-Company Patterns",
      "header": "Current Cross-Company Patterns (engineering) (9847 tokens)",
      "content": "## Current Cross-Company Patterns (engineering) (9847 tokens)",
      "relevance": "32%"
    },
    {
      "layer": 2,
      "layer_name": "Company Context & Preferences",
      "header": "AI Platform Requirements",
      "content": "### AI Platform Requirements\n- **Core principle: \"Use AI wherever it makes the candidate, recruiter, or hiring manager's job easier\"**\n- Real backend processing, not just UI labels\n- All AI provider failover chains must include ALL available models\n- TTS chain: OpenAI → Riva → Magpie Multilingual → Magpie Flow → Magpie Zeroshot → FastPitch → browser fallback\n- LLM chain includes: Qwen 72B, DeepSeek V3.1, DeepSeek R1, QwQ, Gemma 3 27B\n- **Failover routing must actually switch to backup providers when primary is down** — `? → ?` in failover logs indicates broken routing logic\n- **Voice answer processing:** Stale React closures in audio callbacks cause \"no speech detected\" (0/10 responses) — must use ref mirrors for state variables\n- **OpenAI token budget: 100K tokens/day hard cap** — auto-failover to NIM models when limit reached (proactive budgeting, not circuit breaker failure)",
      "relevance": "25%"
    }
  ]
}

